//print middle element of array


public class MiddleElement 
{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 };
        int n = arr.length;

        if (n % 2 == 0) {
            System.out.println("The array has an even number of elements, so there is no middle element.");
        } else {
            int middleIndex = n / 2;
            int middleElement = arr[middleIndex];
            System.out.println("The middle element is: " + middleElement);
        }
    }
}


/*
explanation of the code:

Define an array of integers.
Calculate the length of the array (number of elements).
Check if the array has an even number of elements. If so, print a message stating that there is no middle element.
If the array has an odd number of elements, calculate the index of the middle element using integer division.
Access and print the middle element of the array.
This code determines and prints the middle element of the array, handling both even and odd-length arrays.
*/
